{"cursor":"15758","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\nThe 'International Marxist Tendency' ('IMT') is an international Trotskyist\norganisation founded by the late Ted Grant and his followers following their\nbreak with the Committee for a Workers International in the early 1990s. The\nwebsite is edited by Alan Woods. The site is multilingual, and publishes\ninternational current affairs articles written from a Marxist perspective, as\nwell as a large number of historical and theoretical articles.\n\nThe IMT is led by Woods, Rob Sewell and Lal Khan. It was founded as the\n'Committee for a Marxist International', but has\nreferred to itself as the International Marxist Tendency since 2006.\nThe Tendency is active in over 30 countries worldwide.\n","linknr":357,"url":"International_Marxist_Tendency","recorded":1362675198,"links":31,"instances":["england_and_wales","politician","uk"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Trotskyist political internationals","International Marxist Tendency|","Trotskyism","Communism","Marxism","Political internationals","Trotskyist organisations|","Left-wing internationals"],"headings":["Origin","Theory and Tactics","Activity","2009–2010 Splits","Publications","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/IMT.png/160px-IMT.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b8/In_defence_marxism.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Logo_of_the_Fourth_International.svg/75px-Logo_of_the_Fourth_International.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/Alanwoodsconhugochavez.jpg/220px-Alanwoodsconhugochavez.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wiki